Last time it was Yohan Cabaye, next time it will be Moussa Sissoko. There is only so much a man can take.

He was manager of the month last month, having lifted Newcastle from the foot of the table with a six-game winning run, before losing 1-0 at West Ham on November 29. Since then, they have beaten leaders Chelsea — the only team to do so this season — but lost 1-0 at home to Sunderland. It is typical of their frustrating, rollercoaster form.

Alan was always a couple of wins from a crisis.

