But, as a manager — and it’s the same as a player — you know when your time is up. This is good timing for Alan and he is joining a good club.

Yes, Palace are a smaller club than Newcastle (and they are 10 points worse off) but he will revel in the freedom of a job where he can actually manage. I wish him well.

Palace have been interested before, but this was the right time. Yes, he faces a relegation battle but he enters a transfer window with an owner who will listen to his ideas.

In the end, you go where you’re wanted.

